Uses of Class
sbml2modelica.preprocessing.PreprocessingManager

  • Packages that use PreprocessingManager 
    Package Description
    sbml2modelica.preprocessing
    This package contains a set of classes defining methods for pre-processing operations on an SBML Model.

    • Uses of PreprocessingManager in sbml2modelica.preprocessing

      Subclasses of PreprocessingManager in sbml2modelica.preprocessing 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  CompartmentPreprocessingManager
      A CompartmentPreprocessingManager manipulates data in an SBML Model in order to make it easier the conversion of SBML Compartments into AbstractCompartments.
      class  EquationPreprocessingManager 
      class  EventPreprocessingManager
      The EventPreprocessingManager performs a series of operations to ensure that the Events in the Model are in a certain standard form.
      class  FunctionPreprocessingManager 
      class  ModelPreprocessingManager
      A ModelPreprocessingManager examines a SBML Model and sets up or deletes some informations and structures that simplify the conversion into the AbstractModel.
      class  ParameterPreprocessingManager
      A ParameterPreprocessingManager manipulates data in an SBML Model in order to make it easier the conversion of SBML Parameters into AbstractParameters.
      class  ReactionPreprocessingManager
      A ReactionPreprocessingManager manipulates data in an SBML Model in order to make it easier the conversion of SBML Reactions into AbstractReactions.
      class  SpeciesPreprocessingManager
      A SpeciesPreprocessingManager manipulates data in an SBML Model in order to make easier the conversion of SBML Speciess into AbstractSpeciess.
      class  SpeciesReferencePreprocessingManager
      A SpeciesReferencePreprocessingManager manipulates data in an SBML Model in order to make it easier the conversion of SBML SpeciesReferences into AbstractSpeciesReferences.
      class  SupportPreprocessingManager 
      class  SyntaxPreprocessingManager
      A SyntaxPreprocessingManager pre-processes a SBML Model in order to handle those identifiers that could conflict with some Modelica keyword.
